eeper is found across Southwestern Australia, as far north as Shark Bay, and through to South Australia, as far east as the Eyre Peninsula. The population is heavily concentrated towards the wheatbelt and the south-west corner of WA in and around Perth, becoming more dispersed further east and inland. Open eucalypt forest and woodland are its preferred habitat. References External links Image at ADW [1]", "shortSummary": "The rufous treecreeper (Climacteris rufus) is a species of bird in the family Climacteridae. It is endemic to Australia.", "locations": ["Southwest Australia", "鯊魚灣", "南澳大利亚州", "艾爾半島"], "lat": -25.5, "lng": 113.5, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/95/Climacteridae_-_Climacteris_rufa.jpg/960px-Climacteridae_-_Climacteris_rufa.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-climacteris", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-climacteris-rufus", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-climacteris", "species": "taxonomy-species-climacteris-rufus"}, "expandable": true, "x": -211.35, "y": -403.35, "z": 83.08}], "links": [{"key": "bird-rufous-treecreeper-8f4d1fc3__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-climacteris-rufus", "source": "bird-rufous-treecreeper-8f4d1fc3", "target": "taxonomy-species-climacteris-rufus", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-climacteris-rufus__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-climacteris", "source": "taxonomy-species-climacteris-rufus", "target": "taxonomy-genus-climacteris", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Rufous treecreeper 属于属 Climacteris。"}]}
